# üß† SQL Notes: Learning the `WHERE` Clause

The `WHERE` clause is used to **filter records** based on specific conditions. It returns only the rows that meet the condition(s) you specify.

---

## ‚úÖ Basic Syntax
```sql
SELECT column1, column2, ...
FROM table_name
WHERE condition;


-- 1Ô∏è‚É£ Customers who spent more than $3000
SELECT *
FROM customers
WHERE total_money_spent > 3000;

-- 2Ô∏è‚É£ Customers from the city of Scranton
SELECT *
FROM customers
WHERE city = 'Scranton';

-- 3Ô∏è‚É£ Customers born after January 1, 1985
SELECT *
FROM customers
WHERE birth_date > '1985-01-01';

-- 4Ô∏è‚É£ Products with fewer than 30 units in stock
SELECT *
FROM products
WHERE units_in_stock < 30;
